        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 9:27AM CDT by NWS Midland/Odessa TX</headline>
        <description>At 926 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
McDonald Observatory, or 9 miles northwest of Fort Davis, moving
northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
McDonald Observatory, Davis Mountains State Park, Buffalo Trail Scout
Camp, Black Mountain, and Star Mountain.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Persons in campgrounds should consider seeking sturdy shelter until
this storm passes.</instruction>
